[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/fourth_suit_forcing"]
[Student "S"]
{With both 4-card minors you open 1\D. Partner responds 1\S.  

You cannot support \Ss with only 3 of them. Instead you bid 2\C. Partner says 2\H.  

This is FSF, asking you to further describe your hand, and you have a problem. You do have a \H stopper so you COULD bid 2NT. You also have 3 \Ss so you COULD bid 2\S. Either way might turn out best, but that \HK looks pretty lonesome so you choose 2\S and partner raises to 4\S.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:KJ3.QT975.AQ96.6 T86.AKJ.842.T752 975.63.KT.AKQJ83 AQ42.842.J753.94"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "3NT"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
1H pass 2C pass 2D pass 2S pass 2NT pass 3NT pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: N, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 0, nRot: 1, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "aa6b6262c9670f43cb77c6e58464d5d7fb4b0815b4f35c42931a379fdfdc8327"]
[Category "Bidding Conventions"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "bidding_conventions/fourth_suit_forcing"]
[Student "S"]
{You respond 2\C. Partner rebids 2\D. What is your next bid? 

With 13 HCP and that \C suit you could jump to 4\C. However, that would sail you right past 3NT which is very likely to turn out your best game. Rather than rebid \Cs, find out whether partner has \Ss stopped by using FSF.

You bid 2\S and partner then says 2NT. Where do you go from here? 

It couldn't have worked out better. Notrump played from partner's side. You bid 3NT.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
